  <a href="#1" id="1">
   GENOCIDE IN PAKISTAN
  </a>
  <a href="#2" id="2">
   Prime Minister Benazir Bhutto on May 23, 1990 accused India of waging "genocide" in secession-minded Kashmir and of trying to start a war with Pakistan to deflect attention.
  </a>
  <a href="#3" id="3">
   "India is indulging in genocide," Ms. Bhutto said at a news conference on May 23, 1990 after returning from a weeklong tour of eight Moslem countries in the Middle East and North Africa.
  </a>
  <a href="#4" id="4">
   Ms. Bhutto returned late on May 22, 1990 from visits to Iran, Turkey, Syria, Jordan, North Yemen, Egypt, Libya and Tunisia, a high-profile diplomatic offensive to drum up support for Pakistan's stand on the Kashmir issue.
  </a>
